KAIZER Chiefs have confirmed their first signing in the January transfer period. On Tuesday Chiefs parted ways with defender Lorenzo Gordinho and midfielder james Kotei who failed to break it in the Amakhosi setup. The club have now confirmed that they have snapped up Kenyan midfielder, Anthony Akumu Agay.  The 27-year-old holding midfielder joined Amakhosi on a free transfer after he was released by Zambian outfit ZESCO United. Player Signings!We would like to welcome a new Glamour Boy - Akumu Agay to the Amakhosi Family.#Amakhosi4Life #KaizerChiefs50 #WelcomeAgay pic.twitter.com/n2JQddc7iD 